comment_on_borrowed:
The derivational suffix and the word for ‘prison’ are borrowed from Russian, but the derivation is probably created in Saami; otherwise the Russian source word would be t’uremščik ‘﻿prison officer’.
The word replaced an older North Germanic loanword (vāŋŋg)
replaced older North Germanic loan lahk
could also be derived from loanword sūdt ‘court’
ON seiðr is probably a borrowing from Saami

or derived diminutive from older loan kōrab ‘box’ (< Russian korob) according to the Russian model korob-ka <-- [box-DIM]
clearly borrowed from Ru. kófe; but coffee was probably known before (like in Scandinavia), but I’m not certain if an older loanword was replaced
